MISRA C++ Rule 15.3.1
Exceptions shall be raised only after start-up and before terminations of the program.

GCC has a -Wterminate warning, to check whether dtor throws any exception.
See gcc/testsuite/g++.dg/warn/Wterminate1.C:

```cpp
struct A
{
  ~A()
  {
    throw 1;			// { dg-warning "terminate" }
  }
};

int main()
{
  try { A a;  }
  catch (...) {}
}
```

See gcc/c-family/c.opt:

```
Wterminate
C++ ObjC++ Warning Var(warn_terminate) Init(1)
Warn if a throw expression will always result in a call to terminate().
```

This check covered bad2 & bad3, but not bad1.
